Hi , 
We have tested this issue . DisplayCaps and displayCaps both are working fine .

Note that the displayCaps property begins with a lowercase letter, which differentiates it from the DisplayCaps object that it returns

*Test Code*
{code}
Ti.API.info('Ti.Platform.displayCaps.density: ' + Ti.Platform.displayCaps.density);
Ti.API.info('Ti.Platform.DisplayCaps.dpi: ' + Ti.Platform.displayCaps.dpi);
Ti.API.info('Ti.Platform.displayCaps.platformHeight: ' + Ti.Platform.displayCaps.platformHeight);
Ti.API.info('Ti.Platform.DisplayCaps.platformWidth: ' + Ti.Platform.displayCaps.platformWidth);
{code}

*Log*
{code}
[INFO] :   Ti.Platform.displayCaps.density: xxhigh
[INFO] :   Ti.Platform.DisplayCaps.dpi: 480
[INFO] :   Ti.Platform.displayCaps.platformHeight: 1776
[INFO] :   Ti.Platform.DisplayCaps.platformWidth: 1080
[INFO] :   Ti.Platform.displayCaps.logicalDensityFactor: 3
{code}

Thanks
